        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 1 at 6:00PM EDT until August 1 at 6:15PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 600 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 14 miles east of Uptown Charlotte to 14 miles
northeast of Indian Land to 7 miles west of Monroe, moving southeast
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and power lines.

Locations impacted include...
South Charlotte, Matthews, Mint Hill, Indian Trail, Stallings, Lake
Park, Hemby Bridge, The Arboretum, Weddington, and Fairview In Union
County.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
